Our Organisation  RMIT is a global university of technology design and enterprise. Our mission is to help shape the world through research innovation teaching and engagement and to create transformative experiences for our students getting them ready for life and work.  Situated within the College of Science Engineering and Health the School of Science provides over 45 bachelor and postgraduate programs and undertakes world class research across the disciplines of physical sciences mathematical sciences and computer science.  One of RMITs top-performing research schools we deliver research that addresses the real life questions essential to Australias innovation agenda. Our high-quality teaching programs inspire students to pursue careers in a range of industries including health materials technology food geospatial and surveying environmental analysis banking and commerce as well as computing and IT roles and research and development across a wide range of areas.  The School has staff students and facilities on both the City and Bundoora campuses has 300 staff 327 higher degree research students 3347 coursework students and an annual budget of $120 million.  The position will be aligned with the Discipline of Computer Science and IT part of one of Australia’s largest and leading educational facilities in the field. In the 2017 QS University Rankings by discipline RMIT University was ranked top-100 globally for Computer Science and Information Systems. RMIT University prides itself on the quality of its graduates achieved through programs that have a strong emphasis on both theory and practice.  RMIT University is an Athena SWAN member and the College of Science Engineering and Health is central to driving improvements in gender equality diversity and inclusion particularly in the Science Technology Engineering Mathematics and Medicine (STEMM) disciplines.   The Role and Responsibilities  The Professor is a senior academic and eminent researcher in the specialist field contributing significantly to teaching and research outputs building capability of staff and promoting strong academic performance. The Professor will provide high level research leadership developing and leading research project teams and programs and fostering a vibrant research culture. He or she will be required to develop a high-quality and productivity-driven research network across RMIT and with external national and global partners. The Professor will also make a significant contribution to teaching and learning in the discipline with the aim of improving learning outcomes for students. The Professor will make significant contributions to the planning and strategic direction of the School taking on major academic leadership roles involving participation in various committees within the School College and University and external to the University as appropriate.  This specific position calls for an international leader in the area of Data Science as a subfield of Computer Science. In particular the candidate will provide vision and strategic leadership for the Big Data and Data Analytics research group and for the Master of Data Science. Moreover the candidate will be expected to collaborate closely with RMIT University’s research framework implemented via the Enabling Capability Platforms in particular the platform on Information and Systems (Engineering).  The Professor will be a researcher/academic of international standing in Data Science or related sub-discipline so as to be a role model and an effective mentor for other academic staff.   Skills & Experience Required   To be eligible to apply candidates must have a PhD in the relevant field.  Candidates should have demonstrated research distinction and an internationally recognised research track record in computational Data Science e.g. Big Data Management and Access Data Analytics Machine Learning or associated areas as evidenced by regular publication in the highest-quality relevant international venues related to Data Science a proven ability to sustain and grow Research Groups and Centres through the attraction of external funding and demonstrated strong engagement with industry and other external organisations.   To Apply   For further information please contact Associate Professor Lawrence Cavedon at lawrence.cavedon@rmit.edu.au or visit our website at  http//yourcareer.rmit.edu.au  and search using job ref # 557082.   Applications close on Wednesday 31st May 2017.   Applicants are requested to separately address the key selection criteria as outlined in the Position Description. Our Organisation  RMIT is a global university of technology design and enterprise. Our mission is to help shape the world through research innovation teaching and engagement and to create transformative experiences for our students getting them ready for life and work.  The Education Portfolio is headed by the Deputy Vice-Chancellor Education and Vice President who leads the planning and implementation of the Universitys strategies related to RMITs academic programs and the RMIT student experience. The Portfolio is responsible for services to support the quality of RMIT programs including the professional development of academic staff continuous improvement of the student experience learning and teaching outcomes and the management of learning and research information sources. The Education Portfolio plays a key role in empowering students to access education participate actively in the life of the University and achieve successful and fulfilling lives beyond graduation. The provision of a stimulating and satisfying experience for students is a priority for the University.   The Role and   Your Responsibilities  The Data Scientist undertakes research analysis design and data-driven visualization to create models and assets that informs RMIT on actions and opportunities that emerge through data analysis and interpretation. The role applies a blend of business analysis statistics computer science and education sector experience to draft success stories out of data sets that are diverse and distributed. The role supports RMIT Studios by identifying and proactively implementing the use of data from a variety of sources. The Data Scientist is responsible for designing approaches to sampling experimentation advanced (modern) statistical analysis triangulation data base-design applying ethical standards and evaluating the impact and success of data analysis. This role works closely with other analytic team members for the coordination of the development management analysis interpretation and preparation of data sets databases reports papers presentations visualizations and briefings related to the analysis and reporting of learning and teaching data. The Data Scientist will act as a change agent working with client environments to leverage mature and incorporate data products services and new capabilities.   Skills & Experience Required  You will have proven experience working with multiple data sets and distributed computing tools coupled with a track record of solving analytical problems using quantitative approaches that include programming logic. Your demonstrated experience in the implementation of data analytics and/or evaluation methods for business improvement will be essential to your success in this role. Furthermore your strong and proven understanding of data science practice particularly in sampling experimentation advanced (modern) statistical analysis triangulation and database-design along with your ability to collaborate effectively in an inter-disciplinary team in data analytics to produce actionable recommendations to various stakeholders is important to this role. We have an exciting opportunity for an Analyst to be a part of our Innovation Research & Reform team within the Freight Strategy & Planning Branch of Transport for NSW.    Reporting to the Manager Data Integration and Analytics the position plays a key role in supporting the other members of the Data Integration Unit in collecting maintaining and analysing travel demand customer feedback and operational performance data from the transport networks in New South Wales. We are a values based organisation and employ the most talented people to work together to deliver services for our customers and make NSW a better place to live do business and visit. The ACCC and AER are often called on to fulfil specific additional roles to review monitor or protect markets in almost any sector of the Australian economy. We are currently building some specialist teams and are seeking people with qualifications experience and a strong interest in competition consumer protection and economic efficiency issues. We are seeking specialists across a range of disciplines at classifications from APS 4 to Executive Level 2.  What are we looking for? The ACCC and AER is seeking applications from people with skills in economics; quantitative analysis; consumer protection competition and regulatory law; finance; commerce; accounting or related fields.  We need The immediate aim of this recruitment is to immediately appoint people to specialist teams for new projects and vacancies created by internal staff moving to these projects. Additionally we want to build a list of qualified and experienced people suited to the ACCC and AERs work so that we can rapidly fill permanent and temporary vacancies that arise over the next 12 months. Successful candidates will have a strong interest in the ACCC and AERs goals to  About the ACCC and AER The ACCC is an independent Commonwealth statutory authority whose role is to enforce the Competition and Consumer Act 2010 (the CCA) and additional legislation promoting competition fair trading and regulating national infrastructure for the benefit of all Australians. The AER is an independent body responsible for regulating energy markets and networks under national legislation and rules. The AER has its own Board separate to the ACCC and is supported by staff engaged exclusively on energy matters. It also shares access with the ACCC to specialist legal and economic experts.  Duties At the APS classifications people will a. review submissions for mergers by assessing and reviewing mergers to prevent structural changes to a market that substantially lessen competition. b. review applications for authorisation and notification of certain anti-competitive conduct to evaluate if such arrangements or conduct may result in a net public benefit and warrant exemption from the Competition and Consumer Act 2010. c. review investigate gather interpret analyse assess distil key issues and make recommendations based on  i. information and evidence identified and gathered by the ACCC/AER  ii.technically complex revenue proposals from regulated businesses  iii.tactical intelligence obtained through the use of a suite of intelligence gathering tools and techniques  iv.submissions from stakeholders including market participants governments and consumer groups  v.market incidents and matters in regulated markets relevant to the Competition and Consumer Act 2010 and other regulatory instruments under which the ACCC and AER have responsibilities. d.apply the tools available to us to resolve matters (including education administrative undertakings court enforceable undertakings infringement notices recalls and litigation) and use judgement to determine the circumstances in which it is suitable to use these tools. e.review developing and advocating policy changes. f.prepare correspondence to regulated entities and other external stakeholders governance papers market reports guidelines and instructions to external legal service providers. g.contribute to the development and implementation of effective compliance strategies to raise awareness and influence business behaviour.   How to apply When applying youll be asked to upload your resume you will also be required to respond to the following two behavioural questions with a maximum response of 400 words per question.  1. Tell us about a time you assessed a large amount of information in a short period of time. How did you review investigate interpret analyse assess and/or distil the key issues? What was the outcome of your work? (400 words)  2. Tell us about a time when you were responsible for preparing a written piece of work. What steps did you take to compile the information and how did you ensure your document was suited to its intended audience? (400 words)  I recently applied for a job. Do I need to apply again? Maybe. The selection outcomes for processes that were advertised externally after 13 January 2017 (3 months) will be automatically applied to this process. A list of these processes is available here . If the opportunity you applied for is not on this list or you would liketo extend the duration work areas and or location(s) you can be considered for then you will need to submit another application. If you are an applicant in one of these processes and do not wish for your assessment to be automatically included please let the People and Culture team know by emailing recruitment@accc.gov.au .   Notes This employment opportunity is open to all Australians.  Candidates who are seeking full time or part-time opportunities will be considered and are encouraged to apply.senior people who can lead teams and projects build organisational capability and provide high-level technical skills; highly capable people with the skills to take carriage of and deliver projects; and specialist lawyers and economists to provide expert advice across a range of ACCC/AER functions. maintain and promote competition and remedy market failure  protect the interests and safety of consumers and support fair trading in markets promote the economically efficient operation of use of and investment in monopoly infrastructure increase our engagement with the broad range of groups affected by what we do.

Duties  At the APS classifications people will a. review submissions for mergers by assessing and reviewing mergers to prevent structural changes to a market that substantially lessen competition. b. review applications for authorisation and notification of certain anti-competitive conduct to evaluate if such arrangements or conduct may result in a net public benefit and warrant exemption from the Competition and Consumer Act 2010. c. review investigate gather interpret analyse assess distil key issues and make recommendations based on  i. information and evidence identified and gathered by the ACCC/AER  ii.technically complex revenue proposals from regulated businesses  iii.tactical intelligence obtained through the use of a suite of intelligence gathering tools and techniques  iv.submissions from stakeholders including market participants governments and consumer groups  v.market incidents and matters in regulated markets relevant to the Competition and Consumer Act 2010 and other regulatory instruments under which the ACCC and AER have responsibilities. d.apply the tools available to us to resolve matters (including education administrative undertakings court enforceable undertakings infringement notices recalls and litigation) and use judgement to determine the circumstances in which it is suitable to use these tools. e.review developing and advocating policy changes. f.prepare correspondence to regulated entities and other external stakeholders governance papers market reports guidelines and instructions to external legal service providers. g.contribute to the development and implementation of effective compliance strategies to raise awareness and influence business behaviour.   How to apply  When applying youll be asked to upload your resume you will also be required to respond to the following two behavioural questions with a maximum response of 400 words per question.  1. Tell us about a time you assessed a large amount of information in a short period of time. How did you review investigate interpret analyse assess and/or distil the key issues? How did you present your findings? What was the outcome of your work? (400 words) 2. Tell us about a significant project or piece of work that you took the lead on. How did you lead and guide others to achieve the desired outcome? (400 words) I recently applied for a job. Do I need to apply again?  Maybe. Duties At the APS classifications people will a. review submissions for mergers by assessing and reviewing mergers to prevent structural changes to a market that substantially lessen competition. b. review applications for authorisation and notification of certain anti-competitive conduct to evaluate if such arrangements or conduct may result in a net public benefit and warrant exemption from the Competition and Consumer Act 2010. c. review investigate gather interpret analyse assess distil key issues and make recommendations based on  i. information and evidence identified and gathered by the ACCC/AER  ii.technically complex revenue proposals from regulated businesses  iii.tactical intelligence obtained through the use of a suite of intelligence gathering tools and techniques  iv.submissions from stakeholders including market participants governments and consumer groups  v.market incidents and matters in regulated markets relevant to the Competition and Consumer Act 2010 and other regulatory instruments under which the ACCC and AER have responsibilities. d.apply the tools available to us to resolve matters (including education administrative undertakings court enforceable undertakings infringement notices recalls and litigation) and use judgement to determine the circumstances in which it is suitable to use these tools. e.review developing and advocating policy changes. f.prepare correspondence to regulated entities and other external stakeholders governance papers market reports guidelines and instructions to external legal service providers. g.contribute to the development and implementation of effective compliance strategies to raise awareness and influence business behaviour.   How to apply When applying youll be asked to upload your resume you will also be required to respond to the following two behavioural questions with a maximum response of 400 words per question.  1. Tell us about a time you assessed a large amount of information in a short period of time. How did you review investigate interpret analyse assess and/or distil the key issues? What was the outcome of your work? (400 words)  2. Tell us about a time when you were responsible for preparing a written piece of work. What steps did you take to compile the information and how did you ensure your document was suited to its intended audience? (400 words)  I recently applied for a job. Do I need to apply again? Client Details Work for one of Australia strongest brands with a promising and exciting future ahead. Market leading and attractive salary package. Exciting brand new offices by the end of 2017. Business on the verge of huge acquisition.

The ACCC and AER are often called on to fulfil specific additional roles to review monitor or protect markets in almost any sector of the Australian economy. We are currently building some specialist teams and are seeking people with qualifications experience and a strong interest in competition consumer protection and economic efficiency issues. We are seeking specialists across a range of disciplines at classifications from APS 4 to Executive Level 2.  What are we looking for? The ACCC and AER is seeking applications from people with skills in economics; quantitative analysis; consumer protection competition and regulatory law; finance; commerce; accounting or related fields.  We need The immediate aim of this recruitment is to immediately appoint people to specialist teams for new projects and vacancies created by internal staff moving to these projects. Additionally we want to build a list of qualified and experienced people suited to the ACCC and AERs work so that we can rapidly fill permanent and temporary vacancies that arise over the next 12 months. Successful candidates will have a strong interest in the ACCC and AERs goals to  About the ACCC and AER The ACCC is an independent Commonwealth statutory authority whose role is to enforce the Competition and Consumer Act 2010 (the CCA) and additional legislation promoting competition fair trading and regulating national infrastructure for the benefit of all Australians. The AER is an independent body responsible for regulating energy markets and networks under national legislation and rules. The AER has its own Board separate to the ACCC and is supported by staff engaged exclusively on energy matters. It also shares access with the ACCC to specialist legal and economic experts.  Duties At the APS classifications people will a. review submissions for mergers by assessing and reviewing mergers to prevent structural changes to a market that substantially lessen competition. b. review applications for authorisation and notification of certain anti-competitive conduct to evaluate if such arrangements or conduct may result in a net public benefit and warrant exemption from the Competition and Consumer Act 2010. c. review investigate gather interpret analyse assess distil key issues and make recommendations based on  i. information and evidence identified and gathered by the ACCC/AER  ii.technically complex revenue proposals from regulated businesses  iii.tactical intelligence obtained through the use of a suite of intelligence gathering tools and techniques  iv.submissions from stakeholders including market participants governments and consumer groups  v.market incidents and matters in regulated markets relevant to the Competition and Consumer Act 2010 and other regulatory instruments under which the ACCC and AER have responsibilities. d.apply the tools available to us to resolve matters (including education administrative undertakings court enforceable undertakings infringement notices recalls and litigation) and use judgement to determine the circumstances in which it is suitable to use these tools. e.review developing and advocating policy changes. f.prepare correspondence to regulated entities and other external stakeholders governance papers market reports guidelines and instructions to external legal service providers. g.contribute to the development and implementation of effective compliance strategies to raise awareness and influence business behaviour.   How to apply When applying youll be asked to upload your resume you will also be required to respond to the following two behavioural questions with a maximum response of 400 words per question.  1. Tell us about a time you assessed a large amount of information in a short period of time. How did you review investigate interpret analyse assess and/or distil the key issues? What was the outcome of your work? (400 words)  2. Tell us about a time when you were responsible for preparing a written piece of work. What steps did you take to compile the information and how did you ensure your document was suited to its intended audience? (400 words)  I recently applied for a job. Do I need to apply again? Maybe. The selection outcomes for processes that were advertised externally after 13 January 2017 (3 months) will be automatically applied to this process. A list of these processes is available here . If the opportunity you applied for is not on this list or you would liketo extend the duration work areas and or location(s) you can be considered for then you will need to submit another application. If you are an applicant in one of these processes and do not wish for your assessment to be automatically included please let the People and Culture team know by emailing recruitment@accc.gov.au .   Notes This employment opportunity is open to all Australians.  Candidates who are seeking full time or part-time opportunities will be considered and are encouraged to apply.senior people who can lead teams and projects build organisational capability and provide high-level technical skills; highly capable people with the skills to take carriage of and deliver projects; and specialist lawyers and economists to provide expert advice across a range of ACCC/AER functions. maintain and promote competition and remedy market failure  protect the interests and safety of consumers and support fair trading in markets promote the economically efficient operation of use of and investment in monopoly infrastructure increase our engagement with the broad range of groups affected by what we do.

The ACCC and AER are often called on to fulfil specific additional roles to review monitor or protect markets in almost any sector of the Australian economy. We are currently building some specialist teams and are seeking people with qualifications experience and a strong interest in competition consumer protection and economic efficiency issues. We are seeking specialists across a range of disciplines at classifications from APS 4 to Executive Level 2.  What are we looking for? The ACCC and AER is seeking applications from people with skills in economics; quantitative analysis; consumer protection competition and regulatory law; finance; commerce; accounting or related fields.  We need The immediate aim of this recruitment is to immediately appoint people to specialist teams for new projects and vacancies created by internal staff moving to these projects. Additionally we want to build a list of qualified and experienced people suited to the ACCC and AERs work so that we can rapidly fill permanent and temporary vacancies that arise over the next 12 months.  Successful candidates will have a strong interest in the ACCC and AERs goals to  About the ACCC and AER The ACCC is an independent Commonwealth statutory authority whose role is to enforce the Competition and Consumer Act 2010 (the CCA) and additional legislation promoting competition fair trading and regulating national infrastructure for the benefit of all Australians. The AER is an independent body responsible for regulating energy markets and networks under national legislation and rules. The AER has its own Board separate to the ACCC and is supported by staff engaged exclusively on energy matters. It also shares access with the ACCC to specialist legal and economic experts.  Duties At the Executive Levels people will At the APS classifications people will a. review submissions for mergers by assessing and reviewing mergers to prevent structural changes to a market that substantially lessen competition. b. review applications for authorisation and notification of certain anti-competitive conduct to evaluate if such arrangements or conduct may result in a net public benefit and warrant exemption from the Competition and Consumer Act 2010. c. review investigate gather interpret analyse assess distil key issues and make recommendations based on  i. information and evidence identified and gathered by the ACCC/AER  ii.technically complex revenue proposals from regulated businesses  iii.tactical intelligence obtained through the use of a suite of intelligence gathering tools and techniques  iv.submissions from stakeholders including market participants governments and consumer groups  v.market incidents and matters in regulated markets relevant to the Competition and Consumer Act 2010 and other regulatory instruments under which the ACCC and AER have responsibilities. d.apply the tools available to us to resolve matters (including education administrative undertakings court enforceable undertakings infringement notices recalls and litigation) and use judgement to determine the circumstances in which it is suitable to use these tools. e.review developing and advocating policy changes. f.prepare correspondence to regulated entities and other external stakeholders governance papers market reports guidelines and instructions to external legal service providers. g.contribute to the development and implementation of effective compliance strategies to raise awareness and influence business behaviour.   How to apply When applying you will be asked to upload your resume and submit a statement of claims that is no more than 800 words.  When preparing your statement of claims please take into consideration the role and duties and detail instances from your past that demonstrate how you meet the selection criteria. The AER has its own Board separate to the ACCC and is supported by staff engaged exclusively on energy matters. It also shares access with the ACCC to specialist legal and economic experts.  Duties At the Executive Levels people will At the APS classifications people will a. review submissions for mergers by assessing and reviewing mergers to prevent structural changes to a market that substantially lessen competition. b. review applications for authorisation and notification of certain anti-competitive conduct to evaluate if such arrangements or conduct may result in a net public benefit and warrant exemption from the Competition and Consumer Act 2010. c. review investigate gather interpret analyse assess distil key issues and make recommendations based on  i. information and evidence identified and gathered by the ACCC/AER  ii.technically complex revenue proposals from regulated businesses  iii.tactical intelligence obtained through the use of a suite of intelligence gathering tools and techniques  iv.submissions from stakeholders including market participants governments and consumer groups  v.market incidents and matters in regulated markets relevant to the Competition and Consumer Act 2010 and other regulatory instruments under which the ACCC and AER have responsibilities. d.apply the tools available to us to resolve matters (including education administrative undertakings court enforceable undertakings infringement notices recalls and litigation) and use judgement to determine the circumstances in which it is suitable to use these tools. e.review developing and advocating policy changes. f.prepare correspondence to regulated entities and other external stakeholders governance papers market reports guidelines and instructions to external legal service providers. g.contribute to the development and implementation of effective compliance strategies to raise awareness and influence business behaviour. RESEARCH SCIENTIST – MOLECULAR GENETICS The position of Research Scientist – Molecular Genetics is part of the Agriculture Victoria Research Division’s Genomics & Cellular Sciences team in the Employment Investment & Trade Group. The Employment Investment and Trade Group delivers programs and services to grow the Victorian economy. Its focus is on creating jobs and raising incomes through industry development targeted investment and increasing the export value of Victorian firms. This position is part of a team developing improved genomics technologies that will accelerate pulse improvement. As Research Scientist - Molecular Genetics you will be responsible for the development and implementation of methods and computational tools for association genetics and genomic selection in pulse crops. You will also design and assist in large scale field and glasshouse based trials. This position which reports to the Senior Research Scientist within the molecular genetics team will have strong linkages to the pulse breeding programs conducted for Pulse Breeding Australia. To be successful in this role you will demonstrate knowledge of statistical and numerical genetics and experience in the development and application of advanced computational tools for analysis of genomic and phenomic datasets. You will have the skills to design and assist in the management of large scale field and glasshouse trials and project management experience. A degree in agriculture science molecular genetics quantitative genetics computational biology or a related field is required for this position. For a confidential discussion please call Sukhjiwan Kaur Senior Research Scientist – Molecular Genetics on 03 9032 7117. For further information on the position please see the attached position description. To apply please click the ‘Apply Now’ button below. All applications must address the Key Selection Criteria outlined in the position description. Our Organisation  RMIT is a global university of technology design and enterprise. Our mission is to help shape the world through research innovation teaching and engagement and to create transformative experiences for our students getting them ready for life and work.  The Education Portfolio is headed by the Deputy Vice-Chancellor Education and Vice President who leads the planning and implementation of the Universitys strategies related to RMITs academic programs and the RMIT student experience. The Portfolio is responsible for services to support the quality of RMIT programs including the professional development of academic staff continuous improvement of the student experience learning and teaching outcomes and the management of learning and research information sources. The Education Portfolio plays a key role in empowering students to access education participate actively in the life of the University and achieve successful and fulfilling lives beyond graduation. The provision of a stimulating and satisfying experience for students is a priority for the University.   The Role and   Your Responsibilities  The Data Scientist undertakes research analysis design and data-driven visualization to create models and assets that informs RMIT on actions and opportunities that emerge through data analysis and interpretation. The role applies a blend of business analysis statistics computer science and education sector experience to draft success stories out of data sets that are diverse and distributed. The role supports RMIT Studios by identifying and proactively implementing the use of data from a variety of sources. The Data Scientist is responsible for designing approaches to sampling experimentation advanced (modern) statistical analysis triangulation data base-design applying ethical standards and evaluating the impact and success of data analysis. This role works closely with other analytic team members for the coordination of the development management analysis interpretation and preparation of data sets databases reports papers presentations visualizations and briefings related to the analysis and reporting of learning and teaching data. The Data Scientist will act as a change agent working with client environments to leverage mature and incorporate data products services and new capabilities.   Skills & Experience Required  You will have proven experience working with multiple data sets and distributed computing tools coupled with a track record of solving analytical problems using quantitative approaches that include programming logic. Your demonstrated experience in the implementation of data analytics and/or evaluation methods for business improvement will be essential to your success in this role. Furthermore your strong and proven understanding of data science practice particularly in sampling experimentation advanced (modern) statistical analysis triangulation and database-design along with your ability to collaborate effectively in an inter-disciplinary team in data analytics to produce actionable recommendations to various stakeholders is important to this role.   To Apply   For further information please contact Pablo Munguia on +61 3 9925 2085 or visit our website at  http//yourcareer.rmit.edu.au  and search using job ref # 555954.   Applications close on Sunday 14 May 2017.   Applicants are requested to separately address the key selection criteria as outlined in the Position Description.   RMIT is committed to being a Child Safe organisation and is an equal opportunity employer. Applications are encouraged from all sectors of the community. C onvenient CBD location Full time Continuing position $91086 - $102580 p.a + super

Our Culture This is a place where you can make a difference in our customers lives through the work you do. We are down-to-earth and open and our focus is firmly on value creation for our end customers and stakeholders not on activities management. Positively impacting the community is important to us and you can give back through fundraising volunteer days and grants. The Role As the  Business Design and Solutions Manager  you will work with personal injury claim Exec GM and Injury Scheme Managers on prioritised initiatives to design business solutions and conduct prototyping. Injury schemes are diverse and hence this role will evangelise introducing Design disciplines such as Human Centric Design Lean and Design led innovation into initiatives delivery. You will thought-lead diverse group of stakeholders across claims portfolio data analytics and other function to agree on current state problem / opportunity and create compelling go-forward approach to tackle the problem or opportunity. The strategic initiatives that you will work on will range from – uplifting customer experience in claims services delivery claims cost optimisation implementing scheme reforms and improving claims handling efficiency. This is a senior role which leads a cross-functional team of Business Design and Solutions Analyst BAs PMs Subject matter experts to contribute to Solution Design and be accountable for prototyping / pilot outcomes. Being part of the Personal Injury Claims Strategy function you will assist in strategy formulation and implementation of the strategy through design thinking and in collaboration with the Personal Injury leadership and Claims Solutions functions. Key responsibilities Required qualifications/experience Benefits If you are seeking a long-term sustainable career Suncorp will provide you with the tools to develop your career and invest in the future. You will benefit from joining a dynamic team who are motivated and professional about what they deliver to clients with a strong focus on execution and who are afforded autonomy and accountability in their day-to-day work. If this sounds like you apply online today. For further information please contact Liam Saif on (07) 3135 4107.Participating in drafting a combined vision and business objectives for Business Design function – the business design is a key link between our strategy to delivery execution Create specific link between Business Design functional tasks and an uplift in performance examples of which include (but may not be limited to) – customer satisfaction employer satisfaction claim duration and costs Assist in researching external benchmarks and markets scenarios to operationalise PIC strategy into specific initiatives aligned to management priority. Specifically utilise Design Thinking to introduce new ways of problem solving and opportunity realisation Conduct (and be responsible for coaching other team members on) current state business problem analysis / opportunity identification utilising a variety of Human centric design (HCD) Design Thinking and Lean tools supported with data analysis. Utilise Agile as a key delivery discipline  Document business case and presentation packs for pursuing new ideas and problem resolution and iterate through obtaining management feedback Build trusted adviser relationships with Personal Injury Claims Leadership team to advise and consult on key strategic priorities relating to claims management Source customer feedback from a variety of sources – NPS complaints feedback to ensure that Customer feedback is responded through our solution design options Total work experience of 10+ years  Degree or other tertiary qualification – Mandatory. Masters of Business Administration – Desired Experience and exposure to Insurance function – Mandatory  Experience and to Personal injury products (workers compensation CTP or Life insurance) – Desired Experience in Human Centric Design Innovation delivery and Strategy – Desired An assertive communicator and facilitator  Experience in driving medium to large scale change initiatives as a programme manager or accountable delivery owner Medium degree of proficiency in PowerPoint and MS Excel (Pivot Filters) – Mandatory. MS Project and Visio – Desired Experience in management consulting in a Big 4 or an internal consulting team – desired Experience in formally practicing Lean Six Sigma Agile Design thinking or Lean Startup – desired

We have an exciting opportunity for a Principal Systems Analyst to be a part of our Finance and Investment team within Transport for NSW. This position plays a key role in planning and delivering projects and improvements in financial information systems and reports to the Principal Manager Systems and Business Support.   We are looking for a Principal Systems Analyst who understands core capital financial terminology and has experience in improving the efficiency integrity and robustness of applications and data..   For more information on this position view the role description here.   About us    At Transport our vision is for a truly integrated transport system that will meet the needs of our customers now and into the future. The Transport portfolio includes Transport for NSW as principal agency with Sydney Trains NSW Trains State Transit Authority and Roads and Maritime Services as our key operating agencies.    We are a values based organisation and employ the most talented people to work together to deliver services for our customers and make NSW a better place to live do business and visit.   Benefits    At Transport we offer employees challenging and rewarding work with opportunities for career progression learning and development and flexibility.    We provide comprehensive staff training through structured programs and provide study assistance to staff pursuing work related courses.   Our commitment to Diversity    TfNSW are committed to building a diverse and inclusive culture across the Transport cluster planning for and promoting diversity. We welcome and encourage applications from diverse community groups and ages including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander LGBTI people with disabilities women and other diversity groups. TfNSW recognises the benefits that such an approach brings for our staff and customers in delivering the future of NSW.   Essential requirements    Tertiary qualification in a relevant discipline or equivalent experience.    Extensive experience in financial systems analysis in a large infrastructure environment preferably in government   Please note  The successful candidate will need to undertake background checks and criminal record checks. Electronic Warfare Submariner  Opportunity  As an Electronic Warfare Submariner operate high-tech threat detection systems while enjoying All that plus meaningful experiences such as joining humanitarian missions and supporting communities in need.  Your role  Your submarine is cruising at periscope depth through international waters in an area where tensions are high. Far away a surface vessel poses a potential threat. In this critical role youll be the first person to detect the threat interpret the electronic signals you receive and relay the information to your Captain.  This could be a typical scenario for you as an Electronic Warfare Submariner in the Navy.  It takes a special kind of resourcefulness to join the Deep Elite living and working with a close-knit team in the unique environment of a Collins Class submarine. But the rewards are many and varied and the onboard camaraderie is like no other.  In this demanding role youll use sensitive computerised electronic receivers that can detect classify identify locate and record electronic emissions (such as radio and radar) in your vicinity. You will be taught how to operate this electronic warfare equipment and how to exploit and defend the electromagnetic spectrum in an extremely complex environment.  Given the limited crew size on submarines every submariner gains the skills and knowledge to multitask on their vessel and react in the shortest possible time to incidents as they occur. This means you will also learn to handle and maintain small arms and perform duties such as If you enjoy combining teamwork with technology have a good eye for detail and work well under pressure this is your chance to embark on a really worthwhile career. Better still youll be working for a dynamic organisation that offers a great lifestyle plus opportunities you simply wont find anywhere else.  So do you think you have the qualities and resolve to become an Electronic Warfare Submariner? Then apply now (below).  Salary  Location Entry Requirements  Medical and fitness guidelines also apply.  How to Apply  Click on the APPLY FOR THIS JOB button to submit your application.
